\h Hosea
\toc1 Hoshea
\toc2 Hoshea
\toc3 Hos.
\mt1 Hoshea
\mt2 (Hosea)
\is1 Introduction
\ip This document is about what was prophesied long ago by the prophet Hoshea (often wrongly known in English as вҖҳHoseaвҖҷ) around 800 before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.) and before Shomron (Samaria) was destroyed by invading armies. The prophets Hoshea and Amos gave similar prophecies to the people in similar period, but Hoshea continued on for several years longer. In those times, Yisrael (Israel) was divided into two countries. The northern part where Hoshea preached continued to be known as Yisrael and was also named as вҖҳEfrayimвҖҷ (the name of a prominent tribe in that northern kingdom). Shomron (Samaria) was its capital city. The smaller, southern part of the former, larger Yisrael was named Yehudah (after the largest tribe in that area).
\ip In this document, Hoshea showed the arguments between those who followed Yahweh, and those who had decided to change their allegiance to idols and other gods. The latter were like Hoshea's disobedient spouse Gomir who left him behind. Also, Hoshea was very sad about how the people argued and worshipped false gods, and no longer trusted their god Yahweh. But in the ending, God again displayed his love towards his people and wanted to bring them back to him. His love for them was very strong, and he revealed this to them through Hoshea's sorrowful speeches, вҖңHow can I give you up, O Efrayim? How can I hand you over, O Yisrael? вҖҰ My heart is turned over within meвҖ”all my compassions are aroused.вҖқ (11:8).
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 Hoshea's marriage and family \ior 1:1вҖ“3:5\ior*
\io1 God's case against Yisrael \ior 4:1вҖ“13:16\ior*
\io1 The promise, and the command to repent \ior 14:1-9\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\p
\v 1 This is Yahweh'sВҰ363569 messageВҰ363567 thatВҰ363571 cameВҰ363572 to Beeri'sВҰ363578 son HosheaВҰ363575 \add (HoseaВҰ363575)\add* in the timeВҰ363579 of Kings Uzziyah, Yotam, AhazВҰ363582, and Hizkiyah, of YehudahВҰ363585 \add (Judah)\add*, \add вүҲand was also during the reign of\add* Yoash'sВҰ363590 son KingВҰ363591 YeroboamВҰ363587 in YisraelВҰ363592 \add (IsraelВҰ363592)\add*.\x + \xo 1:1: a \xt 2Ki 15:1-7; 2Ch 26:1-23; \xo b \xt 2Ki 15:32-38; 2Ch 27:1-8; \xo c \xt 2Ki 16:1-20; 2Ch 28:1-27; \xo d \xt 2Ki 18:1вҖ“20:21; 2Ch 29:1вҖ“32:33; \xo e \xt 2Ki 14:23-29.\x*
\s1 Hoshea's wife and children
\rem /s1 Hosea's unfaithful wife; The Family of Hosea; Hosea's Wife and Children
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 2 When Yahweh first spokeВҰ363595 through HosheaВҰ363598, \add *he\add* told \add *him\add*, вҖңGo and \add вүҲget yourselfВҰ363608 a prostitute for a wifeВҰ363609\add* and have childrenВҰ363611 \add вүҲfrom her\add*, becauseВҰ363613 the \add вүҲcountry\add* is committing flagrant prostitution by forsaking Yahweh.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 SoВҰ363621 he wentВҰ363621 and \add вүҲmarried\add* Divlayim'sВҰ363628 daughterВҰ363626 GomerВҰ363625, and she \add вүҲgot pregnantВҰ363629\add* and bore him a son.
\v 4 ThenВҰ363635 YahwehВҰ363636 told him, вҖңName him Yizre'el, becauseВҰ363641 in a littleВҰ363644 while I'll avenge the bloodВҰ363648 \add shed\add* in the Yizre'el \add valley\add* on Yehu'sВҰ363653 \add вүҲfamily\add*, andВҰ363635 I'll put an endВҰ363654 to the kingdomВҰ363655 of YisraelВҰ363657.\x + \xo 1:4: \xt 2Ki 10:11.\x*
\v 5 \add вүҲAt that time\add* inВҰ363667 the Yizre'el valleyВҰ363667, I'llВҰ363662 breakВҰ363662 Yisrael's \add вүҲmilitary power\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 ThenВҰ363670 \add @Gomer\add* conceivedВҰ363670 again and bore a daughterВҰ363673, and \add @Yahweh\add* told \add @Hoshea\add*, вҖңName her Lo-RuhamahВҰ363679 \add (which means вҖҳNo mercyвҖҷ)\add*, becauseВҰ363680 I'llВҰ363682 no longer have mercy on the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ363687, and I won'tВҰ363681\add* forgive them at all.
\v 7 ButВҰ363695 I'll have mercy onВҰ363701 Yehudah'sВҰ363698 \add вүҲdescendants\add*, andВҰ363695 I'll save them \add so they'll be able to see that it was\add* theirВҰ363702 godВҰ363702 YahwehВҰ363701. (I won'tВҰ363703 save them using \add #bows, swordsВҰ363706, battlesВҰ363707\add*, horsesВҰ363708, or horsemen.)вҖқ
\p
\v 8 After she'd weanedВҰ363711 Lo-RuhamahВҰ363715, she got pregnantВҰ363716 \add again\add* andВҰ363711 bore a \add second\add* son.
\v 9 ThenВҰ363720 Yahweh said, вҖңName him Lo-Ammi \add (which means вҖҳNot my peopleвҖҷ)\add* becauseВҰ363725 you're not my people andВҰ363720 I'm not your god.вҖқ
\s1 Yisrael's restoration
\rem /s1 Israel Is to Be Restored; The Restoration of Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 10 Yet the number of \add вүҲIsraelis\add* will be like the sand on the seashore, which can't be measured or counted. Then instead of being told, вҖҳYou're not my people,вҖҷ they'll be told, вҖҳYou are children of the living god.вҖҷ\x + \xo 1:10: \xt Rom 9:26.\x*
\v 11 The people from \add both\add* Yehudah and Yisrael will be gathered together. They'll appoint one leader for themselves, and they'll \add вүҲcome out of the countries\add* \add where they'd been exiled\add*, because the day of Yizre'el \add (which means вҖҳplanted by GodвҖҷ)\add* will be great.
\c 2
\p
\v 1 вҖңSay to your brothers, вҖҳMy people,вҖҷ and your sisters, вҖҳYou've all been shown compassion.вҖҷ вҖқ
\s1 Yisrael, the prostitute, will be punished
\rem /s1 Israel Punished and Restored; Charges against an Unfaithful Wife; Israel's Infidelity, Punishment, and Redemption; Unfaithful GomerвҖ”Unfaithful Israel
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 2 Contend with your mother, contend, becauseВҰ363784 she's not my wife,
\q1 and nor am I her husband.
\q1 Let her \add вүҲturn her face away from\add* prostitution,
\q1 and \add вүЎcease\add* her adultery from between her breasts.
\q1
\v 3 If she doesn't, I'll strip her naked
\q1 вүҲand expose her like on the day she was born.
\q1 I will make her like the wilderness,
\q1 вүҲand make her like a sun-baked land,
\q1 вҶ’and I'll make her die from thirst.
\q1
\v 4 IВҰ363805 won'tВҰ363803 have mercy onВҰ363798 herВҰ363809 children,
\q1 вҶ’because they're \add вүҲthe products\add* of prostitutionВҰ363809,
\q1
\v 5 because their mother has \add вүҲdabbled inВҰ363830 prostitution\add*вҖ”
\q1 вүҲ\add @the woman\add* who conceived them has acted shamefully.
\q1 \add вүҲYes,\add* sheВҰ363823 had said, вҖңI'llВҰ363821 go after my lovers,
\q1 who give me my bread and my water,
\q1 вүҲmy wool and my flax,
\q1 вүҲ\add and\add* my oil and my drink.вҖқ
\q1
\v 6 Therefore, I'll \add вүҲfence her paths in\add* with thorns.
\q1 I'll build a wall up against her so she can'tВҰ363836 find her way.
\q1
\v 7 She'll \add try to\add* pursue her loversВҰ363854, \add вүҲbut\add* she won't \add be able to\add* \add вүҲcatch up to\add* them.
\q1 вүҲShe'll search for them, \add вүҲbut\add* she won't \add be able to\add* find them.
\q1 Then she'll say, вҖңI'llВҰ363852 goВҰ363852 and return to my first husband,
\q1 вҶ’because it was better for me then than it is now.вҖқ
\b
\q1
\v 8 \add вүҲNo,\add* sheВҰ363878 hadn't known that it was me who gave her the grain, the new wine and the oil,
\q1 вүҲand who lavished gold and silver onВҰ363871 her,
\q1 вҶ’which they then used for Baal.
\q1
\v 9 Therefore I'll take my grain back in its time,
\q1 вүҲand my new wine in its season.
\q1 I'll take away my wool and my flax
\q1 вҶ’that were used to cover herВҰ363884 nakedness.
\q1
\v 10 Now I'll uncover her lewdness \add вүҲas her lovers watch\add*,
\q1 \add вүҲbutВҰ363906\add* no one can rescue her \add вүҲfrom my punishment\add*.
\q1
\v 11 I'llВҰ363925 also put an end to all her mirth,
\q1 her feasts, her new-moon celebrations, her rest days, and all her scheduled festivals.
\q1
\v 12 вҖңI'll destroy her grapevines and her fig trees,
\q1 of which she said, вҖҳThose are my wages that my loversВҰ363946 gave me.вҖҷ
\q1 I'll make them \add вүҲgrow wild\add*,
\q1 вҶ’and then the animals in the countryside will devour them.
\q1
\v 13 I'llВҰ363954 punish her for the feastВҰ363962 days for the Baals,
\q1 when she burnt incense to them,
\q1 when she adorned herself with her rings and jewellery,
\q1 and went after her lovers and forgot me.вҖқ
\mi That is Yahweh's declaration.
\s1 The love of God of his people
\rem /s1 The Lord's Love for Unfaithful Israel; The Lord's Love for His People
\s4 Northern kingdom
\q1
\v 14 Therefore, listen, I'm going to entice her.
\q1 вүҲI'llВҰ363965 bring her into the wilderness and speak tenderly to her.
\q1
\v 15 I'llВҰ363985 give her back her vineyards,
\q1 and the \add depressing\add* Akor Valley\x + \xo 2:15: \xt Josh 7:24-26.\x* as a gateway for hope.
\q1 She'll answer me there as in the daysВҰ363989 of her youthвҖ”
\q1 like at the \add вүҲtimeВҰ363989\add* that she came out of Egypt \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*:
\p
\v 16 вҖңYahweh declares you'll call me, вҖҳMy husband,вҖҷ \add вүҲat the time\add*
\q1 ^and no longer call me, вҖҳMy master \add (Heb. Baal)\add*,вҖҷ
\q1
\v 17 because I'llВҰ364022 remove the names of the Baals from herВҰ364026 mouth,
\q1 and they'll no longer be remembered by their names.вҖқ
\b
\q1
\v 18 вҖңOn that dayВҰ364048 I'll make an agreement for them
\q1 with the animals in the fields,
\q1 with the birds in the sky,
\q1 and with the crawling things onВҰ364048 the ground.
\q1 I'll abolish the bow, the sword, and war from the land,
\q1 and I'll make you lie down in safety.
\p
\v 19 I'll \add вүҲtake you as my wife\add* forever.
\q1 I'll \add вүҲmarry\add* you to me in righteousness and justice,
\q1 in loyal commitment, and in mercy.
\q1
\v 20 I'llВҰ364096 \add вүҲbe faithful to you as my wife\add*,
\q1 and you'll know Yahweh.
\p
\v 21 This is Yahweh's declaration:
\q1 \add вүҲAt that time\add* I'llВҰ364104 answer the skies \add ?withВҰ364109 rain\add*,
\q1 and they'll answer the earth.
\q1
\v 22 The earth will answer the grain, the new wine and the oil,
\q1 and they'll answer Yizre'el \add (which means вҖҳGod sows/plantsвҖҷ)\add*.
\q1
\v 23 I will sow her for myself in the land,
\q1 and I will have mercy on Lo-Ruhamah \add (вҖҳNo mercyвҖҷ)\add*.
\q1 I will tell Lo-Ammi \add (вҖҳNot my peopleвҖҷ)\add*,
\q1 вҖҳYou are my people,вҖҷ
\q1 and they'll say, вҖҳYou're \add #our\add* God.вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 2:23: \xt Rom 9:25; 1Pe 2:10.\x*
\c 3
\s1 Yahweh's love for his people
\rem /s1 Hosea and the Unfaithful Woman; Hosea's Wife Is Redeemed; Hosea's Reconciliation With His Wife; Further Assurances of God's Redeeming Love
\s4 Northern kingdom
\p
\v 1 Yahweh told me, вҖңGo againВҰ364185 \add and\add* loveВҰ364187 a womanВҰ364189 who is lovedВҰ364190 by another man and is an adulteressВҰ364192, even as Yahweh lovesВҰ364193 the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ364197 peopleВҰ364197\add*, even though they turn to otherВҰ364204 godsВҰ364203 and \add ?вүҲhonour them with\add* raisin cakesВҰ364206.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 SoВҰ364209 I boughtВҰ364209 herВҰ364209 for myself for fifteen silverВҰ364213 \add вүҲcoins\add* andВҰ364209 \add вүҲten baskets\add* of barley.
\v 3 I told her, вҖңYou mustВҰ364223 stay with me \add вүҲfor some timeВҰ364221\add*. You mustn't \add вүҲdabble in prostitutionВҰ364226 or mess with\add* any other manВҰ364229. In the same way, I'll be \add вүҲtrue to\add* you.вҖқ
\v 4 Because the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ364241 peopleВҰ364240\add* will \add вүҲcontinue\add* for many daysВҰ364237 without a kingВҰ364243 or princeВҰ364245, a sacrificeВҰ364247 or stone pillarВҰ364249, and an ephodВҰ364251 or household idols.
\v 5 AfterwardsВҰ364254, the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ364257 peopleВҰ364256\add* will returnВҰ364255 and \add вүҲwant to follow\add* Yahweh their godВҰ364262 and DavidВҰ364264 their kingВҰ364265, and in the final daysВҰ364274, they'll comeВҰ364266 trembling to Yahweh and to his goodnessВҰ364272.
\c 4
